commit 5408ba7aa295e43968b31a2d893fae85523a0f3b
Author: Austin McGee <947888+amcgee@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Tue Aug 25 11:39:42 2020 +0200

    chore: create dev build script (#5983)
    
    This adds a development build script which does the following:
    
    - Runs mvn locally (so faster than building in Docker)
    - Builds a Docker image with the resulting WAR file
    - (optionally) runs docker cluster up with the passed cluster name to replace the Core service image in a running d2 cluster instance.
    
    Usage:
    d2 cluster up mytestcluster --dhis2-version 2.34.1 --db-version 2.34 --seed
    ./dhis-2/build-dev.sh mytestcluster
    
    System requirements:
    
    bash @ > 4 (notably not default on Mac)
    coreutils for sha256sum and md5sum (not default on Mac)
    Maven (mvn)
    Docker

commit 06fa4ac5762b88a761e16ca4e3a95f87749fc8d4
Author: Luciano <luciano@dhis2.org>
Date:   Mon Oct 28 08:23:47 2019 +0100

    fix: faster TrackedEntityInstance fetching
    
    - DHIS2-7336
    - Introduced "Aggregate" classes to fetch TEI and the TEI graph using
    JDBC (rather than Hibernate)
    - Created new Repository class that fetch TEI data using the `in` clause, rather
    than one by one
    - Using Futures to asyncronously fetch parts of the TEI graph
    - Current implementation is 19X faster than Hibernate one
    Missing:
    
    - No acl checks
    - Some part of the graph are still missing
    - Geometry is not handled yet

commit 9e4b839e6a067098f77018df4d12de2f1d0c3a80
Author: Lars Helge Øverland <lars@dhis2.org>
Date:   Mon Aug 17 11:38:03 2020 +0200

    feat: Make database audit configurable [DHIS2-9266] (#5931)
    
    Makes the various audit functionality which write audit records to the database configurable through the existing AUDIT_DATABASE / audit.database config key for dhis.conf.
    
    The purpose is to be able to disable database audit logging for use-cases where audit is not required and one wants to avoid the overhead of saving and storing a large amount of audit database records.

    fix: faster TrackedEntityInstance fetching
    
    - DHIS2-7336
    - Introduced "Aggregate" classes to fetch TEI and the TEI graph using
    JDBC (rather than Hibernate)
    - Created new Repository class that fetch TEI data using the `in` clause, rather
    than one by one
    - Using Futures to asyncronously fetch parts of the TEI graph
    - Current implementation is 19X faster than Hibernate one

    - No acl checks
    - Some part of the graph are still missing
    - Geometry is not handled yet

commit bcb34d9e684de1c06dff8b74c29fea6e52a22d6e
Author: Luciano Fiandesio <luciano@dhis2.org>
Date:   Thu Aug 13 08:56:55 2020 +0200

    fix: invoke super.equals() on BaseDimensionalItemObject (#5920)
    
    The `equals` function on `BaseDimensionaltemObject` was using the default equals comparison: `if ( o == null || getClass() != o.getClass() )` which, in case of Hibernate proxied objects, will not work.
    This fix removes that checks and calls the `equals` on the super class (`BaseNameableObject` which uses `isAssignableFrom` to handle proxy classes.

commit 5867c314d2db0f6c835424638d878c0f9626e8bf
Author: Luciano Fiandesio <luciano@dhis2.org>
Date:   Wed Aug 12 14:46:39 2020 +0200

    fix: Use Org Unit uid on Events/Enrollment table creation (#5892)
    
    * fix: Use Org Unit uid on Events/Enrollment table creation
    
    When a Program has a Data Element or TEA of type Organisation Unit, the system was persisting the OU name in the analytics_event_* and analytics_enrollment_* tables.
    
    This was done to fix another issue with Event/Enrollment Line List view, which was showing the Org Unit UID rather than name.
    Persisting the name, rather than the UID, was causing a bug becuase the join with the Org Unit table was broken, if a user selects "Org Unit Field" in the Event table layout (Pivot App).
    
    This fix:
    
    - reverts the change to the JdbcTableManager, so that the Org Unit UID is used in analytics tables
    - adds a new column "<dataelement>_uid" to the event analytics tables, containing the name of the OU
    - modifies the Events query logic to use this new column when querying for events
    
    * chore: renamed test method

commit 9dbd7416caa9aac60a24978501e8e3b1393da2fe
Author: Luciano Fiandesio <luciano@dhis2.org>
Date:   Wed Aug 12 13:54:56 2020 +0200

    fix: handle Period as filter in analytics Indicator queries (#5903)
    
    Fix an issue during the aggregation of the Grid data in Indicator queries: if the Period is used as filter and no
    Period Offset is used in the Indicator, the code generates an invalid Map key.
    Fix the problem by using all the dimension item UID as key components.
    
    // Example
    
    Given a query:
    
    `api/32/analytics.json?dimension=dx:Uvn6LCg7dVU&dimension=ou:ImspTQPwCqd&filter=pe:LAST_12_MONTHS`
    
    There are 2 dimensions (`dx` and `ou`) and one filter (`pe`).
    If the `dx` is an Indicator, the resulting Grid will contain multiple rows (one for each Indicator item), with 3 columns
    
    1) indicator item uiid
    2) ou uid
    3) value
    
    The aggregated Map, that is returned and used by the Expression engine, should  have the following key:
    
    `<indicator item uid>-<ou uid>`

commit 2ed799f33ca26b918ed60473a3f097714f00492e

commit aabb9e9f5260eacdca6146554d4ae35b01448c5b
Author: Luciano Fiandesio <luciano@dhis2.org>
Date:   Tue Aug 4 09:49:06 2020 +0200

    fix: fix Indicator Grid results index resolution (#5872)
    
    * fix: fix Indicator Grid results index resolution
    
    After the introduction of Period Offset (DHIS2-8758), the Indicator data aggregation logic needs to resolve the period
    index withing the aggregated Grid. In case of a query that uses ORG UNIT GROUP SET, the resulting Grid contains multiple
    dimension items for each row and the period index can shift to 2 or 3 position.
    With this fix, a more robust method to identify data and period index is introduced during Indicator grid handling.
    
    ref: DHIS2-9214
    
    * uncomment code

commit 5509a3f08f424a245fac1265edab12cb1ad15630

commit 76570513efd70ad6c626144f723f854aedfe2584
Author: Viet Nguyen <viet@dhis2.org>
Date:   Tue Aug 4 14:40:24 2020 +0700

    fix: AttributeValue performance issue with fields parameter [DHIS2-9059]
    
    This PR fix two issues:
    
    AttributeValue contains only Attribute's uid so for a request as below the FieldFilterService always get the full Attribute object for each AttributeValue. So to fix this, this service will only get the Attribute if the query requires more properties than just Attribute's uid.
    Don't get Attribute
    fields=options[id,name,code,attributeValues]
    Get Attribute
    fields=options[id,name,code,attributeValues[value,attribute[id,name]]
    There is an issue with the LocalCache. It always put new entry into the cache even if the entry is already existed. This slows down the performance of the cache.
    So now this code only puts new entry to cache if it does not exist.

commit 01a4d5120c146dc376d614d5ff31e76679bc6921
Author: Morten Olav Hansen <morten@dhis2.org>
Date:   Mon Aug 3 09:19:11 2020 +0200

commit 5b7a7245d083931148a3783e989b00e9369f0bdc
Author: Luciano Fiandesio <luciano@dhis2.org>
Date:   Tue Jul 28 11:36:31 2020 +0200

    revert: removed Tracker Audit side effect handler (#5850)
    
    The Auditing sub-system is based on Hibernate listeners that intercepts any Hibernate-managed object prior to any persistence-related operation and fire a Audit message to the Auditing sub-system.
    The component that has been removed in this PR repeats the same operation from the listeners, which would cause two audit entries for each persistence operation.

commit b85261219b82ad71593275bc8ecad65d1f01bfa5
Author: Maikel Arabori <51713408+maikelarabori@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Tue Jul 28 11:28:31 2020 +0200

    fix: Casting to Number to avoid class cast exception [DHIS2-8631] (#5853)
    
    Sometimes row.get( valueIndex ) returns long, so we cannot cast to Double. This fix will cast to Number and convert to double in order to avoid the error.

commit 4a0141b03ebca082efd61d2e1352b948126e8b61
Author: Lars Helge Øverland <lars@dhis2.org>
Date:   Tue Jul 14 11:31:26 2020 +0200

    feat: Introduce user lookup API [DHIS2-8749] (#5813)
    
    Introduces a user lookup API. This is intended as a minimal API for user information, which can be used by clients which needs access to basic user information, without exposing sensitive or extensive user information.
    
    The endpoint is located at /api/userLookup. The first method located at /api/userLookup/{id} allows for lookup by either UID, UUID or username and will return exactly one or zero users.
    
    The second method located at /api/userLookup?query={query} allows for querying users by firstname, surname, username and email, and will return many or zero users.

commit 2c5a6f7bbbb00d0e4ff8028fde972fd6f4413f8c
Author: Luciano Fiandesio <luciano@dhis2.org>
Date:   Mon Jul 6 09:24:18 2020 +0200

    feat: Period offset for Indicator formula (#5772)
    
    This feature allows to "shift" by period one or more elements within an Indicator formula.
    
    Given the following Indicator formula:
    
    #{gQNFkFkObU8} + #{MaXD86iob3M}
    
    It is now possible to add a periodOffset() directive, in order to calculate the value for the
    query-specific period based on the declared periodOffset:
    
    (#{gQNFkFkObU8}.periodOffset(-1) + #{MaXD86iob3M}.periodOffset(-1)) - (#{gQNFkFkObU8} + #{MaXD86iob3M})
    
    In the above example, assuming that the Analytics query is executed for the period Feb 2020, the results will calculate the
    value of gQNFkFkObU8 + MaXD86iob3M for January 2020 (offset -1) and subtract the value from February 2020.

commit aa75a25b530d5013d0b309ac8f492828cad456e0
Author: Luciano Fiandesio <luciano@dhis2.org>
Date:   Tue Jun 16 11:14:24 2020 +0200

    fix: Invalid weekly period year reference (#5745)
    
    * fix: Invalid weekly period year reference
    
    This fix corrects an error during the `_periodstructure` generation process. The process assigns the wrong year to a week Period.
    
    Example: `2019-12-31`
    The week of `2019-12-31`, according to the ISO calendar system, belongs to 2020, since 4 or more days of that week fall in 2020.
    
    In order to handle all Weekly Period types uniformly, 3 days are added to a Weekly Period type start date.
    
    Example:
    
    | Weekly Type     | Example Date | Date -> Start Date -> + 3             |
    |-----------------|--------------|---------------------------------------|
    | Standard        | 2019-12-31   | -> 2019-12-31 +3 = 2020-01-03 = 2020  |
    | Weekly Saturday | 2019-12-31   | -> 2019-12-28 + 3 = 2019-12-31 = 2019 |
    | Weekly Sunday   | 2019-12-31   | -> 2019-12-29 + 3 = 2020-01-01 = 2020 |
    | Weekly Thursday | 2019-12-31   | -> 2019-12-26 + 3 = 2019-12-29 = 2019 |
    | Weekly Wed      | 2019-12-31   | -> 2019-12-25 + 3 = 2019-12-28 = 2019 |
    
    ref: DHIS2-5990
    
    * chore: address sonar issue

commit 7f22222f1343fd15c3d12276dd322e92ec846285
Author: Luciano Fiandesio <luciano@dhis2.org>
Date:   Mon May 25 14:34:09 2020 +0200

    fix: prevent audit StackOverFlow error with Relationship (#5622)
    
    * fix: prevent audit StackOverFlow error with Relationship
    
    The Auditing component fails to serialize to Json self-referencing TEIs.
    When a TEI (tei A) has a relationship with another TEI (tei B), and tei B
    references tei A, the Jackson parser fails with a Stack Overflow Error.
    
    This fix uses a Jackson annotation on the RelationshipItem class that "forces"
    the serialization to only serialize the "simple" information of the linked Tei and
    avoid recursion into the "relationship" attribute
    
    * chore: reverted changes to DefaultAuditObjectFactory
    
    Same changes implmented by later PR: https://github.com/dhis2/dhis2-core/pull/5624

commit b542fa21172c116db2f0933f61cf364fef0ddaf2

commit e9c8211bea99ab4ba279b80c38d1fda30e00ad6c
Author: Luciano Fiandesio <luciano@dhis2.org>
Date:   Mon Apr 6 16:42:12 2020 +0200

    fix: calculate metadata pagination total pages (#5324)
    
    * fix: calculate metadata pagination total pages
    
    - DHIS2-8754
    
    This fix addresses an issue introduced with this PR: https://github.com/dhis2/dhis2-core/commit/b132f0685b9040f194ee5bb932fc08317e0a6aa8
    
    The `Pager` object requires a "total" value in order to properly calculate the number of pages. The "total" is **now** passed to the `Pager` object and it's calculated by executing a count query using the same filter and sorting criteria used for the original query.
    If the Metadata Query engine requires an in-memory query (because a filter or sort field is non-persisted), then the pagination is executed in memory by the Query Engine and no longer in the controller.
    
    * fix: use Restassured assertions

commit 3e0aa6ee33955ca86f4f85b6dc1ae57bc7cabbd5
Author: Gintare Vilkelyte <vilkelyte.gintare@gmail.com>
Date:   Thu Apr 2 14:27:37 2020 +0200

    ci: Test multiple docker images (#4847)
    
    This PR centralizes caching configuration for Analytics at 'HTTP layer' and 'data layer'.
    Some other minor changes were needed in order to keep these set of changes more meaningful.
    
    Important breaking changes:
    
    With this change, the application will stop reading the property analytics.cache.expiration in dhis.conf. So this setting will have no effect anymore. The users will only be able to set the expiration time through the System Settings endpoint.
    
    The default expiration time (TTL) for both the 'HTTP layer' (see WebCache.java) and Analytics is 1 minute (because we will not read from dhis.conf anymore). The default value is defined at SettingKey.CACHE_STRATEGY. This value is now centralized and used by both Web and Analytics (for FIXED expiration time only).

commit 20ab6060826b63a6ca8a371ea259d62c4594d573
Author: Maikel Arabori <51713408+maikelarabori@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Thu Apr 2 14:24:57 2020 +0200

    feat: Unifies the config for fixed caching at web layer and analytics layer [DHIS2-8389] (#5244)
    
    This commit centralizes caching configuration for Analytics at 'HTTP layer' and 'data layer'.
    Some other minor changes were needed in order to keep these set of changes more meaningful.
    
    Important breaking changes:
    
    With this change, the application will stop reading the property analytics.cache.expiration in dhis.conf. So this setting will have no effect anymore. The users will only be able to set the expiration time through the System Settings endpoint.
    
    The default expiration time (TTL) for both the 'HTTP layer' (see WebCache.java) and Analytics is 1 minute (because we will not read from dhis.conf anymore). The default value is defined at SettingKey.CACHE_STRATEGY. This value is now centralized and used by both Web and Analytics (for FIXED expiration time only).

commit 2ddd56959af60973db581671fa849a1511aade32
Author: Lars Helge Øverland <lars@dhis2.org>
Date:   Tue Mar 24 17:02:00 2020 +0100

    fix: Ensure caching for queries with missing settings (#5161)
    
    A performance problem is currently caused by the system making a high number of user setting queries for user settings which have no value nor default value. This causes a transaction and database lookup to happen, and consumes a fair amount of CPU because they happen frequently e.g. as part of the translation solution.
    
    This change introduces a dedicated SerializableOptional class which is suitable for wrapping a Serializable and achieves "negative caching", which implies that null responses will be cached. This is suitable for user and system settings because there are quite few possible values. By default, caches skip null values, and so this prevents the system from re-checking missing user setting values very frequently. The SerializableOptional object is better suited as cache key than Optional as it can be type-safe.

commit 5d1c6a4b81b16365a80ae3fc69fb237446221d58

    - DHIS2-8402
    - Reverted removal of TrackerEntityInstance Attribute Audit REST endpoint (`/audits/trackedEntityDataValue`)
    - Introduced security check for TrackerEntityInstance Attribute Audit REST endpoint, so that only DataElement for which the user has access to are returned.

      endpoint

    - Restored calls from `DefaultTrackedEntityInstanceService` to
      `DefaultTrackedEntityInstanceAuditService`
    - Moved `TrackerAccessManager` from `dxf2` package to `service-core` to avoid circular dependency
    - Fixed wrong placement of test classes in dhis-support-artemis project

commit a3e7d67ec99469e2de045eb03407aca3fc41f2ab
Author: Luciano Fiandesio <luciano@dhis2.org>
Date:   Mon Mar 9 12:07:07 2020 +0100

    style: automatic code formatting on commit (#5022)
    
    - TECH-305
    - Introducing "speedy-spotless" to automatically format Java code upon
      commit (see doc:
    https://docs.google.com/document/d/1kOKCSmm3vXyHKkO6mllvvdYlBK793WHG6OGWEASfHe8/edit)
    
    - from the root dhis2 directory, execute
    
    `mvn speedy-spotless:install-hooks`
    
    This will install the pre-commit hook that invoke Spotless only on
    modified Java files

    fix: fetch unique values during metadata import (#5014)
    
    - DHIS2-8267
    - Introduce new component that fetches only unique attributes for a
      Metadata object during Metadata import pre-heat (instead of executing
    something like "select * from table" now the system executes "select
    column_a, column_c from table".
    - Force the query to be read-only to prevent Hibernate to syncronize the
      data with the database
    - Refactored Metadata import validation into Validation Rules, in order
    to improve testability and "code-cleaness"

    feat: Analytics aggregation type with multiple data elements as filter (#4710)
    
    * feat: Analytics handles multiple filter Data Elems
    
    - DHIS2-7797
    - This change allows an Analytics query to retain the aggregation type
    when multiple Data Elements having the same data type and aggregation
    type are used as query filters.
    If the filter Data Elements have different aggregation type or data
    value then the system will default to SUM aggregation type and NULL data
    type
    
    * Update DefaultQueryPlanner.java

commit 854f360f19992498f8245cb90b1ab9b99d945d9f
Author: Lars Helge Øverland <lars@dhis2.org>
Date:   Mon Jan 13 14:12:25 2020 +0100

    feat: Continuous scheduling and analytics table job (#4627)
    
    * Introduces scheduling of jobs with _fixed delay_, i.e. jobs that run continuously with a specified number of seconds delay in between the executions. This includes a new `SchedulingType` enum for `JobType`, which indicates whether the job is triggered by cron expression or with a fixed delay between executions. There is a 10 seconds default delay between when _fixed delay_ jobs are scheduled and invoked the first time.
    
    * Introduces a continuous analytics table job, which updates the _latest_ analytics table partition continuously, and updates the full analytics table once per day.
    
    * The latest analytics table delay is specified in seconds using the `delay` property on `JobConfiguration`. The time of the full analytics table update is specified using the `hourOfDay` property on `ContinuousAnalyticsJobParameters`.

Author: Luciano Fiandesio <luciano@dhis2.org>

    fix: Use Program Indicators to validate orgUnitField (#4673)
    
    * fix: use Prg. Indicators to validate orgUnitField
    
    - DHIS2-7552
    - When validating the orgUnitField value the system now takes in
    consideration the event that a Program may be null and also checks for
    Program Indicators. If the EventQueryParams contains Program Indicators,
    the system runs the same validation against all the Programs associated
    to the Program Indicators. If at least one fails, the entire validation
    fails.

commit dc18ccb49ddd052015a8669c9768f56add197403
Author: Luciano Fiandesio <luciano@dhis2.org>
Date:   Thu Dec 19 14:35:15 2019 +0100

    feat: Log sessionid in log4j logs [DHIS2-7963] (#4413)
    
    * feat: log sessionid in log4j logs
    
    Logs an hashed version of the Session Id as part of a log entry.
    The Session Id is placed into the log4J MDC framework (based on thread
    local) and passed to the logs.
    This feature is *disabled* by default. To enable set:
    
    `monitoring.requestidlog.enabled = on`
    
    in DHIS2 configuration.
    Additional parameters:
    
    `monitoring.requestidlog.hash` : controls the default hash algorithm
    (defaultL SHA-256)
    `monitoring.requestidlog.maxsize`: controls the max size of the request
    id (default: no max size)

commit 27a6ef1670d37625fac9fc00d2e28ac000ce4b66
Author: Viktor Varland <viktor@dhis2.org>
Date:   Tue Dec 10 17:58:16 2019 +0100

    ci(docker): add escape hatch to only build default container (#4590)
    
    ONLY_DEFAULT=1 ./docker/build-containers.sh <image> <identifier>
    
    The above would result in only the default core image with tomcat being built,
    which is handy in local testing situations where you only need to build a single
    image, and want to avoid the storage overhead of building all Tomcat images we
    provide.

commit 00b7ce04d19bf8adbed780aad5dd851f520fd510
Author: netroms <netroms@gmail.com>
Date:   Tue Dec 3 01:05:13 2019 +0100

    fix: Add custom authentication logger without sensitive info (#4405)
    
    * fix: Remove LoggerListener from the security.xml
    
    The org.springframework.security.authentication.event.LoggerListener should not be used in production since it leaks Session ID into the logger.
    
    Issue: [DHIS2-7602]
    
    * fix: Remove LoggerListener from the security.xml
    
    The org.springframework.security.authentication.event.LoggerListener should not be used in production since it leaks Session ID into the logger.
    The spring LoggerListener is replaced by a new custom listener, this new listener hashes the session id to prevent it from leaking into the logs.
    To also be able to log auth events from http basic, the http-basic config in security.xml is augmented with a new AuthenticationDetails object that capture the x-forwarded-for header if present.
    
    Issue: [DHIS2-7602]

commit db1011a6b7ee816eb55c168b2543ef87cb57c14e
Author: netroms <netroms@gmail.com>
Date:   Mon Nov 18 15:04:53 2019 +0100

    fix: Fix Powermock issue with JDK11 (#4189)
    
    The test DefaultCompleteDataSetRegistrationExchangeServiceTest will not run without use of PowerMockIgnore on "javax.xml.*"
    Without this fix running tests results in this error:
    "java.lang.IllegalAccessError: Class javax/xml/stream/FactoryFinder(unnamed module 0x00000000C107C170) can not access class jdk/xml/internal/SecuritySupport(module java.xml) because module module java.xml does not export package jdk/xml/internal to module unnamed module 0x00000000C107C170"
    Tested on: (Java.net) 11.0.5-open and (AdoptOpenJDK 11.0.4.j9-adpt)

commit 1fe6d6362598fa2ac21ac5b44444e99a7fb3b08f
Author: netroms <netroms@gmail.com>
Date:   Sat Nov 16 18:53:08 2019 +0100

    fix: Check if username is locked in 2FA auth (#4186)
    
    Before this fix, the ip was used to check if the username was locked due to too many failed login attempts, enabled via the config variable "keyLockMultipleFailedLogins" (default value is false)
    This would not work since only username is added to the failed login counter cache when a failed login attempts occur.
    
    Issue: [DHIS2-7861]

    - Moved the logic that detects if nested Indicators have a cyclic dependency to the Analytics validation step

commit 50abe15f948b8c76489909a3c2b1ddb52c749e7c
Author: Luciano Fiandesio <luciano@dhis2.org>
Date:   Thu Nov 14 11:47:55 2019 +0100

    fix: Improve cyclic detection algorithm for nested indicators (#4149)
    
    - DHIS2-6901
    - Introduced Tree structure to represent nested indicators,
    so that the certain edge cases can be detected
    - The cyclic detection algo now traverses the tree of nested indicators,
    when a new Indicator is added (e.g. IndA -> IndB -> IndC --> IndA) and
    throws an Exception if the newly added indicator is found in the tree.

commit c5e2a3d1351becb9f9fe9ff954fb7ff758d7193d
Author: netroms <netroms@gmail.com>
Date:   Mon Nov 11 13:11:05 2019 +0100

    feat: Add endpoint for disable/enable users (#4152)
    
    This commit introduce two new endpoints on the UserController: "/uid/disable" and "/uid/enable"
    Before this commit disable/enable could only be done via a PATCH call (sending a json user object) to the UserController.
    This commit also incorporate the fix from issue [DHIS2-7358] (expire a users's active session(s) in the Spring SessionRegistry).
    
    Issue: [DHIS-7823]

commit 9083a78099303f9b8ed5d3f4fa2884f669012f1d
Author: netroms <netroms@gmail.com>
Date:   Mon Nov 11 12:15:42 2019 +0100

    fix: Expire a user's active session when disabled (#4150)
    
    Before this change, when we disabled a user in the user admin, an already logged in user would still be "active/usable" until the session expired.
    Now, when we disable a user via the user admin we retrieve the users's active session from the "SessionRegistry" and expire them.
    
    Issue: [DHIS2-7358]

commit 37eee37907eb72972262b1db95e7c1dc3bf7742b
Author: Luciano Fiandesio <luciano@dhis2.org>
Date:   Thu Sep 19 14:32:01 2019 +0200

    Add ategory Option Groups support in indicator expressions (#3599)
    
    * feat: use CategoryOptionGroup in indicator formulas
    
    - DHIS2-3308
    - Allow using CategoryOptionGroup UID (COGUID) in indicator formulas, so
    that a COGUID is "expanded" to multiple CategoryOptionCombos UIDs.
    - COGUID are expanded as follows:
    
    case 1: #{DEUID.COGUID.AOCUID}
    resolved to: #{DEUID.COCUID1.AOCUID} + #{DEUID.COCUID2.AOCUID} + #{DEUID.COCUID3.AOCUID} + ...
    
    where DEUID = Data Element UID, COCUID1.. = a list of
    CategoryOptionCombos corresponding to the provided COGUID, AOC =
    AttributeOptionCombo
    
    case 2: #{DEUID.COCUID.COGUID}
    
    resolved to: #{DEUID.COCUID} + #{DEUID.COCUID1} + #{DEUID.COCUID2} + #{DEUID.COCUID3} + #{DEUID.COCUID4}
    
    where COCUID1,2,3... are resolved by fetching all COCUID by COGUID
    
    case 3: #{DEUID.COG1UID.COG2UID}
    reolved to: #{DEUID.COCUID1} + #{DEUID.COCUID2} + #{DEUID.COCUID3} + #{DEUID.COCUID4}
    
    where COCUID1 and COCUID2 are resolved from COG1UID and COCUID3 and COCUID4 are resolved from COGUID2
    
    * chore: removed commented code

commit bb4f92beee29d88a271c04dab64168528ee1a97d
Author: Lars Helge Øverland <lars@dhis2.org>
Date:   Mon Aug 26 00:30:00 2019 +0200

    Add near-real-time analytics API support (#2975)
    
    The main goal of this PR is to make data more quickly available in analytics tables. The overall approach is to introduce a new analytics table partition which holds only the data captured since last full analytics table update, and always include this partition in analytics queries. This can reduce the lag between analytics runs from hours down to seconds.
    
    The PR does the following:
    
    * Introduces a new partition table called "latest". This holds the latest data, i.e. data added or updated since last full analytics table generation. The latest partition uses a "year" value of 0.
    * The latest partition is dropped and rebuilt on each run (like the regular analytics partitions).
    * For each analytics table run, the system checks whether there is new, updated or deleted data since last run.
    * When considering whether there is new data, the timestamp of the start of this process is used to guarantee no overlap between runs.
    * Data which is updated or deleted through runs is deleted from any of the analytics partitions (including old data).
    * A new synthetic unique identifier column is added to the analytics tables for the purpose of deleting updated/deleted data.
    * The system checks whether new data exists since last update of the latest partition, and if not, aborts the update.
    
    The scheduling part is yet to be done. Triggering the "latest" partition can be done through the API like this:
    
    ```
    POST /api/31/resourceTables/analytics?lastYears=0&skipResourceTables=true
    ```

commit dbb180b2e8674f57664e9954a9d000ad1b17ea3b
Author: Austin McGee <947888+amcgee@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Mon Aug 26 00:15:26 2019 +0200

    fix: Don't try to extract a non-existant zip file (#3668)
    
    When the container is restarted (not re-created) it crashes because the WAR file has already been unzipped and removed.  Only try to explode the WAR file if it exists.
    
    Also extract some commonly-used directories and files to variables for easier editing in the future.

commit 3ed6b69eaecd83e45267828b2ffab9685f444fea
Author: Lars Helge Øverland <lars@dhis2.org>
Date:   Sun Aug 25 12:14:04 2019 +0200

    Use geometry type instead of point in event analytics tables (#3669)
    
    - In event analytics, use GEOMETRY instead of GEOMETRY_POINT as column type for org unit type columns. Org unit uses geometry data type and hence using point in analytics tables would often crash when encountering polygon type org units.
    - Added quoting of org unit geometry columns for consistency.
    - Code style fixes.

commit 99f839d7dd9e49a2de616dab112c715015eabe0b
Merge: e9e777449e 3b1f56b7db

commit 3b1f56b7dbd4a2aa10ee072d3f19c519ffe167a0
Author: Volker <volker@dhis2.org>
Date:   Thu Apr 25 11:37:31 2019 +0200

    Resolve performance issues with large category option requests (#3212)
    
    * Adds missing index for queries from options of categories.
    
    - Solves parts of the issues of DHIS2-6491.
    - Executed queries require a big amount of full table scans of
      categories_categoryoptions. This is solved by an index that can
      perform index-only queries in a lot of cases.
    
    * Specifies batch querying for dependencies of categories.
    
    - Solves parts of the issues of DHIS2-6491.
    - Frequently accessed dependencies of category options are fetched
      in batches from database.
    - Possible side effect: More data could be queried than before. If for
      example user accesses or user group accesses have been queried
      conditionally only depending on other ACLs, these are returned also
      in a batch now.
    - The amount of database statements that are executed are reduced
      drastically.
    
    * Caches authority evaluations of schemas.
    
    - Solves parts of the issues of DHIS2-6491.
    - getAuthorityByType() is accesses a big amount of times when
      doing ACL evaluations. For the issue DHIS2-6491 the method required
      more than 10 seconds execution time and was indicated by Hot Spot
      of YourKit.
    
    * Clones unmodifiable authority lists for ACL evaluations.
    
    * Caches user credentials computed values.
    
    - Solves parts of the issues of DHIS2-6491.
    - getAllAuthorities() and isSuper() is accessed a big amount of times
      when doing ACL evaluations. For the issue DHIS2-6491 the method
      required more than 10 seconds execution time and was indicated by
      Hot Spot of YourKit.
    
    * Optimized Hibernate PostgreSQL JSONB type deepCopy() method .
    
    - Solves parts of the issues of DHIS2-6491.
    - In case the value to be copied is null, Jackson does not need to be
      used to serialize and deserialize. null can be returned immediately.
    - Instead of writing and reading value as a string for deep copying,
      value can be written and read to and from a token buffer directly.

commit bcf205d9f8600aa41fc94cfce943302b7303b8f4
Author: Lars Helge Øverland <lars@dhis2.org>

commit ab8a53c712eceef9aaf74702d8164d1cded32112
Author: Volker <volker@volsch.eu>
Date:   Mon Apr 22 07:43:27 2019 +0200

    Fix issue with missing database information in system info (#4670)
    
    * Fixes issue with missing database information in system info (#4670)
    
    - Database information is never cloned, but sensitive information is
    reset to null on requests where user has not authority ALL. Database
    information must be cloned before sensitive information is reset for
    current request.
    
    - URL is parsed to retrieve database name. Database name can be omited
    with current PostgreSQL driver versions. In order to avoid further
    adaptions of the parse algorithm and default value handling for upcoming
    releases of the PostgreSQL JDBC driver, the resulting database name is
    retrieved from database.
    
    - URL may contain the name of the user that is used to connect to
    database. To get the final user, the database can be used to return the
    user name.
    
    - Database version and URL have not been marked for output.
    
    * Replaces clone by bean utils copy properties (#6561)

    Added skipSharing for metadata export with dependencies (#5292) (#3026)
    
    - The same export parameters that are used for normal export are now
      used for export with dependencies (even if just some of the options
      are used). This enables future extensions.
    - The download parameter can be added to all endpoints in order to
      get the metadata as an attachment.
    - All fields will be excluded in all skip sharing exports:
      "user", "publicAccess", "userGroupAccesses", "!userAccesses",
      "externalAccess" (at the moment just some of them, caused by filter).

commit 4a4d0bcda27ea5c040732d440530d6cd1909da49
Author: Lars Helge Øverland <lars@dhis2.org>
Date:   Mon Mar 18 10:59:01 2019 +0100

    Use simplified value type in analytics metadata (#3023)
    
    In analytics metadata response for items, the value type property can now be any of these:
    
    - NUMBER
    - BOOLEAN
    - DATE
    - FILE_RESOURCE
    - COORDINATE
    - TEXT
    
    This to expose an appropriate level of detail to the client. More detailed value types such as "positive integer" are folded under NUMBER, etc.

commit 14506d4cbc0f1b48cf67ec417e33e0caf84751dd
Author: Viktor Varland <viktor@vardevs.se>
Date:   Fri Sep 28 23:32:14 2018 +0200

    Continuous delivery of frontend applications (#2185)
    
    * Use Node and NPM to install frontend web applications
    
    * Basic support for using NPM and Node to manage webapps
    
    This allows us to remove Maven from the frontend workflows, instead
    publishing frontend applications directly to NPM.
    
    The `dhis-web-apps` maven project then executes one command with NPM and
    one with Node.
    
    1. `npm install`
    2. 'node ./copy-apps.js'
    
    The first installs the dependencies to `node_modules`. In this case all
    our applications would be published to NPM.
    
    The second copies the apps from `node_modules/<app>` to
    `target/dhis-web-apps/<app>` just like the previous JAR-files where
    unpacked to.
    
    There are some benefits to this as I have outlined in:
    https://docs.google.com/document/d/1DTY22D1CDpPQqqFOENkJKhHyhgTT6j8XRgARo84TtwY/edit#heading=h.fxuxtg782lfg
    
    The major ones are:
    
    1. Continuous deployment of web apps
    2. Simplified workflow for app developers
    3. The ability to deploy beta-versions, canary release, deprecate versions, etc.
    4. The ability to freeze versions in the WAR-file
    5. The ability to create custom WAR-file builds with any apps by just
       changing the package.json file.
    6. Reproducible builds and knowledge about what code is running in what
       build
    
    * Commit the correct pom.xml
    
    * Generate the struts.xml
    
    * Get a working maintenance app running
    
    * Use maven-frontend-plugin to dl node/npm build time
    
    * Ignore the generated resources
    
    * Updates to scripts
    
    * Use branches for core resource and maintenance for now
    
    * chore: add deps for apps to package.json
    
    * fix: use prefix for apps
    
    * Update references to plural dashboards to match the app name
    
    * Organize scripts differently, rename index.html to template.html (the result is generated)
    
    * Add name sanitizer to avoid duplication mistakes
    
    * Skip blacklisted apps
    
    * fix: remove legacy deps
    
    * fix: revert removal of messaging redirect
    
    * chore: update lock file
    
    * chore: add build info to index file
    
    * chore: update lock-file
    
    * chore: update all deps to use the master builds

commit 8ecf5fe947448fa1766fc23d517b0dde0838341f
Author: Mohamed Ameen <ameenmk23@gmail.com>
Date:   Tue Mar 27 11:27:50 2018 +0200

    Integrated Spring Session and Shared Cache backed by redis (#1767)
    
    * Integrated spring-session backed by redis
    
    Added provision to enable spring session backed by redis. If redis isnt configured, application will fallback to the default session handling without redis. Added ConfigurationKeys for redis related properties. Used @Conditional to selectively register beans based on redis configuration
    
    * Changed to Java Configurations + Added Caching implementation
    
    Removed xml based configurations for spring sessions and converted them to java based configurations. Enabled component scanning for one package. Added caching implementation which switches between local cache (backed by Caffeine) or shared cache (backed by Redis). Refactored the configurations into the dhis2 support external module rather than dhis2 web commons module
    
    * Integrated shared cache implementation into Security Service and User Settings
    
    * Added logs to identify cache type created at startup
    
    * Incorporated PR review comments.
    
    1. Changed the formatter to avoid splitting implements,extends into new lines.
    2. Builder pattern to create cache instance using a CacheBuilder
    3. Generics to define the value type of the cache
    4. NPE to IllegalArgumentException wherever relevant.
    
    * Fixes for cache abstraction
    
    1. Correctly set ttl for redis keys
    2. Correctly set default value for local caffeine cache
    3. Sensible defaults to cache builder set in constructor
    
    * Fixed comment on user setting cache
    
    * Refactored spring session and cache abstraction
    
    Due to javax.servlet dependencies causing issues in maven test phase, the spring session configuration is refactored and moved into dhis-web-commons module
    
    * Cache expiry disabled by default
    
    Only if the expireAfterAccess or expireAfterWrite is set then cache expiry will be enabled
    
    * Formatting changes
    
    * Removed null checks and boilerplate codes
    
    * Corrected formatting
    
    * Moved cache solution to dhis-support-system module
    
    * Moved redis dependency to dhis-support-system module
    
    * Interfaced CacheProvider and placed in cache package

    DHIS2-434 (#1557)
    
    * WIP
    
    * Enum with initial set of methods, parser and TextPattern model implemented. Tests for all the code
    
    * Added a new endpoint for getting required fields for a pattern; Added service, utils and tests for rendering a pattern
    
    * Added ObjectBundleHook for validating pattern for TEIAttribute
    
    * Refactored a lot of logic out of the enum and into specific Type-classes. Should give more readable and manageable code in the future as the list of method grows
    
    * Improved naming of variables to be consistent accross MethodType and TextPattern. Added validation method for TextPattern
    
    * Added methods for getting required values and rendering with required values to controller
    
    * Simplified and refactored some stuff regarding segments. Added resolving current date
    
    * Added models for reserving values and counting sequences. Added store and test for counting sequences
    
    * wip
    
    * Made TextPattern and TextPatternSegment Immutable; Refactored a lot of code to conform to this, and to also simplify the overall structure; TextPattern can now be stored as jsonb
    
    * wip; reserved value
    
    * wip
    
    * wip; Added tests, ReservedValueService, general refactoring
    
    * WIP; Copyright and author, started ReservedValueTests
    
    * wip
    
    * Minor refactors and tweaks; Added unit tests
    
    * minor
    
    * Added TextPattern as jsonb; Added validation and tests for TPValidationUtils
    
    * wip
    
    * Added importOptions for skipping validation; Added validation; Removed old code and files;
    
    * Added mapping file we still need
    
    * wip
    
    * removed unused enum item
    
    * Changed mapping of ReservedValue, since it was not adding constraint. Added id (might remove it again as we dont really need it). Added most of the upgrade SQL
    
    * Added upgrade sql, deletionhandlers, updated reservedvalue hbm
    
    * Added query param for expiration
    
    * added valueType validation and tests
    
    * Added new method "isReserved" to check if a reservedValue exists. If true, validation will be succcessfull even if pattern is not a match to value
    
    * Added wildcard for RANDOM to get any of digit, uppercase and lowercase
    
    * Added timeout for generation and reservation of values; 30 s
    
    * Fixed comments from Henning
    
    * added * as a valid format for RANDOM. parsing and validation
    
    * Added created, changed expiration to expiryDate, controller now returns ReservedValue, not strings

commit 0188b2f88f887b8a405683e6b89168850e51f4a7
Author: Lars Helge Øverland <lars@dhis2.org>
Date:   Wed Dec 6 18:35:18 2017 +0100

    Analytics table SQL hooks (#1362)
    
    Added support for analytics table SQL hooks. An analytics table hook allows you to execute arbitrary SQL scripts at specific phases during the analytics table generation process.
    
    The following hook phases should are included:
    
    * After resource table generation
    * After analytics table population (before indexing and swapping temp to real table).
    
    It is possible to define the specific analytics table type for each analytics table hook.

commit a5ae6bc5d994a1dec39964665783257083d80bcb
Author: Lars Helge Øverland <lars@dhis2.org>
Date:   Mon Nov 20 17:32:21 2017 +0100

    Analytics, take advantage of table partitioning in analytics queries (#1282)
    
    Analytics engine. Take advantage of new inheritance-based table partitioning in the code for analytics queries. Simplifies and allows for removing special code for partition handling. Queries are now referencing the base table, and uses a special where clause on the yearly table column to allow PostgreSQL scan only the required partitions through constraint exclusion.

    Analytics table partitions with PostgreSQL table inheritance (#1269)
    
    Implements analytics table partitioning using PostgreSQL native table inheritance, having a master analytics table with many table partitions. This provides a master table which can be queried directly, allowing for clients to make queries against analytics tables without considering the partitioning.

commit 8ac0baf7b408b3b32097d7f1cf58848bf82ded57
Author: George Gelaga-King <gb7309@gmail.com>
Date:   Tue Nov 29 11:37:09 2016 +0000

    Refactor: Support dates & comments in DataValueSMS
    
    Dates sent in through the DataValueSMS would get stripped out because they had a hypen (-). For example: 2016-11-29, only the 2016 would make it through, and then be rejected as an unacceptable value. Also, with comments only the first word would make it through and the rest would get stripped out. For example: "Oh my awesome comment", only the "Oh" will get taken without "my awesome comment".

commit c36bccb0d62dd1a376ede9ecd148460471bb7b02
Author: Stian Sandvold <stian@dhis2.org>
Date:   Thu Nov 10 11:44:44 2016 +0100

    Multiple legendsets (#289)
    
    Adds support for BaseDimensionItemObjects to have multiple legend sets.
    Currently returns both the new "legendSets" and the old, single legendSet "legendSet" in api calls to avoid breaking existing apps, since no api versioning can be used for this currently. Should be removed when 225 is no longer supported.
    
    Dataelement
    DataSet
    Indicator
    ProgramIndicator
    TrackedEntityAttribute

commit 0f9d63ed07fb05a47011f0cfe2bd368bead0809a
Author: Halvdan Hoem Grelland <halvdan@dhis2.org>
Date:   Mon Oct 3 17:31:26 2016 +0200

    Various fixes and enhancements to program notifications and tracker service layer. (#190)
    
    * Refactoring. Remove superfluous and repetitious code
    
    * Add missing variable resolvers
    
    * Minor cleanup + add debug statements
    
    * Fix bugs where recipients were not properly populated in ProgramNotificationService
    
    * Add missing i18n strings
    
    * Rename and negate ImportOptions.sendNotifications to ImportOptions skipNotifications. As a result, the default behaviour of our Event endpoints is now to trigger sending any notifications (enrollment, completion etc.). Batch imports and import of historical data should make sure to set the skipNotifications query param to true. Also changed contract in the Tracker service layer to reflect this change and avoid confusion. Additionally did minor refactoring to avoid code duplication in JacksonEventService.

Date:   Mon Sep 26 13:18:48 2016 +0200

    Soft data value deletes (#152)
    
    Introduces a new column deleted on data value which is not null and default false. All datavalue queries include a constraint on datavalue is false. When adding data values, the system checks for previously soft deleted values and when found, merges the new data value with the soft deleted.

commit 402312c69ae7083c39d0e24a29044cf1c7703521
Author: abyot <abyota@gmail.com>
Date:   Fri Sep 23 13:56:20 2016 +0200

    program configuration for expiry of events. Program has three properties: completeEventsExpiryDays - this decides the number of days that needs to be passed for a completed event to be locked after date of completion; expiryPeriodType - this helps to associate an event with particular period (rather start and end dates). The event is then available for editing within this date ranges plus some additional expiryDays. The expiryPeriod also controls whether an event can be created or not. For an event to be valid, it needs to fall within the date ranges of its valid period.
